        "slug": "2022-intern-himanshu-sood-jane-street",
        "content": "\nHimanshu Sood, studying in IIT Kanpur as a BT student in CSE will do\nhis summer internship in Quantitative Trading profile at Jane Street. Here are some brief\ninsights of his.\n\n## Shortlisted Profiles & Companies:\nJane Street - Quant Trading, Quadeye - Quant, Microsoft - SDE\n\n## Insights on the Selection Process\n1. Resume Shortlist\n2. Test - There was a subjective test with questions on probability\n3. Interview Process - There were a total of five interviews, one of which was a preliminary round, and the other four happened consecutively on the final day.\n\nThey mostly tested for knowledge and ability to apply fundamental probability concepts such as linearity of expectation, understanding of probability distributions, etc.\n\n##  Preparation Resources\nA Collection of Dice Problems by Matthew M. Conroy, 50 Challenging Problems in Probability, Brainstellar, LeetCode, CSES Problemset\n\n## Advice for students (dos and don’ts)? \nFor Quant profiles, it’s important to be well versed with Probability concepts (such as\nexpected value and linearity of expectation). They also expect you to be able to do simple\ncomputations quickly and accurately.\n\n",
