        "content": "\r\nHarsh Jain , studying in IIT Kanpur as a BT student in CSE will do\r\nhis summer internship in R&D Associate profile at Samsung Electronics Co., Ltd. Here are some brief\r\ninsights of his.\r\n\r\n## Shortlisted Profiles & Companies:\r\nnan\r\n\r\n## Insights on the Selection Process\r\nOnly one Question from Strings and some projects from my resume were discussed in the technical interview.\r\nTheoretical knowledge of DSA is a good thing to have for smooth technical interview process.\r\nJust be confident and never give one word answers. It's not an objective Question paper which would have a binary answer. Always try to express your answer as a story.\r\n\r\n##  Preparation Resources\r\nI used GFGs for preparing the base. It has the collection of all standard problems and algorithms.\r\nInterviewBit to practice for coding tests and interviews. \r\nI used Brainsteller to prepare for Quant profiles.\r\n\r\n## Advice for students (dos and don’ts)? \r\nDo CP to clear coding tests and have some good knowledge of DSA for clearing interviews. A course on probability is a good thing for Quant profiles. And try to maintain a good CPI ( it will have only good side effects:)\r\n\r\n",
