        "slug": "2023-intern-hisham-hadi-t-google-hardware",
        "content": "\r\nHisham Hadi T, studying in IIT Kanpur as a BTech student in EE will do\r\nhis summer internship in Silicon Engineering Intern profile at Google Hardware. Here are some brief\r\ninsights of his.\r\n\r\n## Shortlisted Profiles & Companies:\r\nnan\r\n\r\n## Insights on the Selection Process\r\nGoogle gives high weightage to previous experience in core when\r\nshortlisting candidates for interview. Having core projects or second\r\nyear core internships is a positive factor\r\nGoogle also looks for something they call Googleyness, which is an\r\nindicator of how good a fit the candidate is to the google culture.\r\n\r\n##  Preparation Resources\r\n1. Prof. Baquer Mazhari’s lectures for ESC201, available on YouTube\r\n2. HDLbits for Verilog practice\r\n3. PYQs of relevant core courses done in IITK\r\n4. Other youtube lectures and channels like Neso Academy\r\n5. Coding from Interviewbit (mainly for other profiles)\r\n\r\n## Advice for students (dos and don’ts)? \r\nDos:\r\n1. Think out loud in interviews. Keep talking through whatever you’re doing to get to the\r\nsolution. For the interviewer, how you reached the answer is just as important as the\r\nanswer you got.\r\n2. The interviewer is not your opponent. Learn to find cues in what they say, they often\r\nnudge us in the right direction.\r\nDon’ts:\r\n1. Don’t try to answer questions from courses that you haven’t studied. Just tell them and\r\nthey will avoid questions from that area.\r\n\r\n",
