        "slug": "2023-intern-riktesh-singh-samsung-research-institute-bangalore",
        "content": "\r\nRiktesh Singh, studying in IIT Kanpur as a B Tech student in EE will do\r\nhis summer internship in R&D (Research and Development)  profile at Samsung Research Institute Bangalore . Here are some brief\r\ninsights of his.\r\n\r\n## Shortlisted Profiles & Companies:\r\nAtlassian - SDE JLR - Core+SDE \r\nGIVA - Analytics Samsung Bangalore – R&D \r\n\r\n## Insights on the Selection Process\r\n1- First 30 min discussion will be on resume, projects done by you and then you may be asked to explain one project of your choice. \r\n2- Then few DSA based questions will be asked. \r\n3- Even if you don't know the answer, try to solve taking your time. Most of the time they will only see your aptitude skills and if you can tell them the right approach to solve the question but you cant solve the problem. They will surely hire you based on your aptitude skills.\r\n\r\n##  Preparation Resources\r\n1- https://usaco.guide/ \r\nHere under the section tab you can find all the resources level wise. \r\n2- https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLauivoElc3ggagradg8MfOZreCMmXMmJ- \r\nLuv cp Playlist \r\nStriver placement questions and his YT playlist \r\nApna college YT playlist for c++ placement prep. \r\n3- https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX- \r\n1vTZKOWEcBTRwAa5CaLPbUHAh5oJfOhQMPUrwGvTJ- \r\nHNiYkwCZnrlcXhe16gcyXmdeubCupGpQqFXq8h/pub?start=false&loop=false&delay \r\nms=60000&slide=id.p1 \r\nLast year SPO intern prep weekly resources and questions\r\n\r\n## Advice for students (dos and don’ts)? \r\n1- In an interview always tell them the naïve approach first then slowly move to the most \r\noptimised solution. \r\n2- In the first month most of the company will ask questions only from graph, trees, BST \r\nand linked list in their interviews. \r\n3- Give mock interviews to your seniors before going for any interview, and don't panic in \r\nfront of HR or your interviewer. Don't call them Sir/Ma'am. They are just 4-5 yrs older than you, so call them by their name and always ask about the interviewer at the end of the interview like what was the first project He/She did in that company? \r\n4- Go through some frequent interview questions and answers on gfg, prepbytes,etc. 5- Before any company's interview try to go through the previous year questions of same \r\ncompany's interviews which are available under gfg interview experience tab. \r\n\r\n",
