        "content": "\r\nShreyansh Sinha, studying in IIT Kanpur as a BS student in MTH will do\r\nhis summer internship in Quant profile at Morgan Stanley. Here are some brief\r\ninsights of his.\r\n\r\n## Shortlisted Profiles & Companies:\r\nTower Research, Uber, Boston Consulting Group, Bain\r\n\r\n## Insights on the Selection Process\r\nPractice Dynamic Programming and Graphs well as most of the questions asked in the coding round or interview will be from this.\r\nPick any one resource and try to complete it throughly before moving to other resource as depth matters more than breadth. Also, practice all the standard questions well and try to form a peer group where you can discuss approaches as it benefits a lot. For puzzles brain-stellar and 50 challenging problems are more than enough. For Consulting roles, case-prep can be done well in 20-25 days.\r\n\r\n##  Preparation Resources\r\nInterviewbit, Brainsteller, 50 challenging problems in probability \r\n\r\n## Advice for students (dos and don’ts)? \r\nTry to be motivated throughout the summers as well as internship drive. Also, if you haven’t done coding before summers then also their is sufficient time so don’t loss hope. All the best for your interns\r\n\r\n",
