        "content": "\nDivyansh Garg, studying in IIT Kanpur as a BT student in CSE will be joining SquarePoint Capital as Infrastructure Engineer. Here are some brief insights of his.\n\n## Shortlisted Profiles & Companies:\n- Graviton (Software Engineer) - JP Morgan (Full-Time Analyst) - NK Securities (Software Engineer)\n\n## Insights on the Selection Process\n- There was first resume shortlist done, followed by an online test in which questions from- Bash and Docker were asked. (Basic Linux bash scripts). Finally, we had interviews.- The interviews were conducted in three rounds. All three interviews were technical. The third interview was with the team manager, so some HR questions type were asked.- The questions asked were fundamental and were related to networking, cryptography, and OS fields. We were not expected to give a precise answer, instead based on your knowledge, youcan form the answers out of thin air.\n\n##  Preparation Resources\n- Leetcode- CP algorithms ((https://cp-algorithms.com/))- Brainstellar\n\n## Advice for students (dos and don’ts)? \n- Start your preparations early. Stay calm. Code Hard.- Solve Inter IIT doc questions of all companies.- Do not put too many projects/interns in your resume, just put the impactfulprojects/internships, and go through every single term in your resume.\n\n",
